Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
I think it is probably a good idea to keep freshmen in campus. Firstly, they may need a chance to get to know each other and make some new friends. They may also need to learn how to live with other people, as well as join their social activities. living on campus would give them great college life experience. What is more, it is usually safer to live on campus.